# OpenCV base container

A base python container with opencv and python flask.

https://opencv.org/

## Build

```bash
export CR_PAT=<personal access token>
echo $CR_PAT | docker login ghcr.io -u darrylcauldwell --password-stdin        
docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 . --tag ghcr.io/darrylcauldwell/face:latest --push
docker pull ghcr.io/darrylcauldwell/face:latest
docker run --name face -d -p 4000:5000  ghcr.io/darrylcauldwell/face:latest
```

## Test an RTSP stream can be captured

```bash
import cv2
rtsp_url = 'rtsp://darryl:cauldwell@192.168.188.2/stream2'
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(rtsp_url)

if not cap.isOpened():
    print("Failed to open RTSP stream.")
else:
    print("RTSP stream opened successfully.")

cap.release()
```
